    slug: "bulugh-ul-maraam-urdu-2-volumes-set-14x21",
    description: `Bulugh ul Maraam — Urdu 2 Volumes Set (14x21) is the Urdu translation of one of the most important and widely studied hadith compilations in the Islamic world, originally authored by the renowned scholar Al-Hafiz Ibn Hajar al-Asqalani (773-852 AH). The original Arabic work, whose full title is Bulugh al-Maram min Adillat al-Ahkam (Attainment of the Objective through Evidences of the Rulings), is a meticulously curated collection of hadith that serve as primary evidences for Islamic legal rulings. Ibn Hajar, who is also the author of the monumental Fath al-Bari (the most celebrated commentary on Sahih al-Bukhari), compiled this work as a practical reference for students and scholars of Islamic jurisprudence, organizing the hadith according to the chapters of fiqh (Islamic law) to make it easy for readers to find the evidences for any specific ruling.

This Urdu translation presents the complete text of Bulugh al-Maram in two volumes, making the work accessible to the vast Urdu-speaking Muslim population that includes readers in Pakistan, India, Bangladesh, and diaspora communities around the world. The hadith are organized into chapters covering the major areas of fiqh, including purification (taharah), prayer (salah), funerals (janazah), zakat, fasting (sawm), Hajj, trade and commerce, marriage and divorce, crimes and punishments, and Jihad. Each chapter begins with the relevant hadith, presented in Arabic with full chains of narration, followed by the Urdu translation and commentary. Ibn Hajar's grading of each hadith is included, indicating whether it is narrated by Al-Bukhari, Muslim, or other collectors, and whether its chain is authentic (sahih), good (hasan), or has some weakness. Where multiple narrations exist for the same ruling, the compiler presents them all, giving the reader a comprehensive view of the available evidence.

The 14x21 centimeter format of this edition is a standard medium size that is convenient for both study and reference. The two-volume set allows for comfortable handling, with the text distributed across volumes in a logical and user-friendly manner. The binding is sturdy, designed to withstand the frequent handling that a reference work of this nature typically receives in madrasahs and personal libraries. The Urdu translation is clear and accurate, preserving the legal precision of the original while remaining accessible to readers who may not be specialists in hadith science. This edition is widely used in Pakistani and Indian madrasahs as a core text in the dars-e-nizami curriculum, and it is equally valuable for individual scholars, imams, and serious students of Islamic knowledge who want a reliable, well-organized collection of the primary hadith evidences for Islamic legal rulings.`,
    metaDescription: "Bulugh ul Maraam Urdu 2 Vol Set by Ibn Hajar al-Asqalani covers hadith evidences for fiqh rulings. Standard 14x21 medium format for madrasahs."
